Durban - eThekwini Municipality has issued a warning to residents to be wary of con-artists posing as municipal workers in order to solicit gifts during the festive season. The city's Tozi Mthethwa, advised residents that Durban Solid Waste staff are strictly prohibited from touting for money or gifts from residents. She added that residents are advised to continue leaving their refuse out on their area's stipulated days as refuse collection will continue throughout the festive season. This includes on Christmas Day, 25 December 2017 and New Yearâ€™s Day, 1 January 2018. "DSW offices will be closed on 25 and 26 December 2017 and on 1 January 2018 but the operational staff will be on duty throughout the festive season providing services to eThekwini residents," Mthethwa said. Daily News